message.content: cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.BIO, cs.CV, cs.NEURON - The paper involves the use of deep learning algorithms for metadata augmentation of RNA expression data, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the study focuses on the analysis of biological data, specifically small RNA expression profiles, which could be categorized under bioinformatics (cs.BIO). The use of backpropagation-based feature importance scores and DeepLIFT method for understanding the biological relevance of sRNAs suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NEURON) in the study.
